WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:01.800
Hello, thanks for joining me

00:00:01.800 --> 00:00:05.000
as we traverse around the country
looking at the weather forecast

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.600
for Thursday, tomorrow, and we will have
a few things to keep an eye on as well.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:11.160
This trough through New South Wales moving

00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:14.880
northwards, pushing some cooler
southerly winds through the state there.

00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:18.680
In fact, we'll be seeing cool southerly
winds across much of southern Australia

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:22.760
getting driven up by this approaching
high pressure area to the south-west

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:25.800
that is going to be moving
towards the country during Thursday,

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:28.800
sticking around for several days
after that as well, leading

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:30.880
to some slightly chilly,
but generally, quite

00:00:30.880 --> 00:00:33.880
settled weather across the southern
half of the country.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:37.200
There is these breaks of really
fine conditions around most of Queensland

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:39.280
where flooding is ongoing,
but if we track further

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:43.040
north across North Queensland,
the Northern Territory and the Kimberley,

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:47.160
we will see showers and thunderstorms
with the risk of heavy rainfall.

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:50.160
For Queensland specifically,
should be a pretty bright day

00:00:50.160 --> 00:00:53.680
from about Townsville,
Bowen, Whitsundays southwards.

00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:58.160
The flood situation across
the east is evolving, but in general

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:01.320
lots of those river levels
are starting to come down now

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:04.440
as it's been a couple of days
since that heavy rain ceased.

00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:07.080
Brisbane should have a sunny day,
quite a warm one as well.

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:08.640
High of 34°C.

00:01:08.640 --> 00:01:09.920
We're looking at similar temperatures

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:12.600
across the south-east
and the southern interior.

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:16.773
Rain, showers and storms expected
across the north through the Herbert and Lower Burdekin,

00:01:16.773 --> 00:01:21.120
North Tropical Coast, Cape York
Peninsula and the Gulf of Carpentaria.

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:24.680
This trough is going to be moving
northwards through New South Wales

00:01:24.680 --> 00:01:26.600
through the morning,
bringing chillier winds.

00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:28.520
So, expect the temperature to drop, actually

00:01:28.520 --> 00:01:30.560
for many places
around the middle of the day,

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:33.520
including in and around Sydney,
we could see those temperatures

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:37.120
fall from the high 20s to the lower 20s
for the afternoon.

00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:40.880
That change in wind and that cooler air
coming up from the south

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:42.560
won't generate much shower activity

00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:46.000
but we could see a few light falls,
particularly from Newcastle northwards.

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:49.200
Can't rule out 1 or 2
light falls elsewhere along the coast.

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:50.200
Fine in the south.

00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:53.520
Fine in the west, with temperatures
a few degrees cooler than recent days.

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:56.880
It's feeling a little cooler
across Victoria as well.

00:01:56.880 --> 00:02:00.720
Southwesterly winds are bringing
a very autumnal feel to the weather

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:05.000
on Thursday, with temperatures
in the high teens to mid 20s.

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:09.040
There'll be a little bit of light rain
caught up in that wind flow as well on

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:10.280
and south

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:13.080
of the Victorian mountain ranges,
so we could see a spot

00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:14.600
or two of right around Warrnambool,

00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:17.240
all the way out to South Australia,
then and through Melbourne

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:19.040
and across parts of Gippsland as well

00:02:19.040 --> 00:02:22.040
but none of that rain
will be heavy or persistent.

00:02:22.440 --> 00:02:24.720
And that same wind,
which is dragging the cooler air

00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:27.720
to Victoria, is doing likewise down here
in Tasmania.

00:02:27.880 --> 00:02:31.920
Temperatures in the teens for Thursday,
a little bit gusty as well.

00:02:32.160 --> 00:02:36.000
The southwesterlies will pepper the west
coast with showers throughout the day.

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:39.400
Hobart might get 1 or 2 light showers,
but there shouldn't be much

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:40.560
in the rain gauges.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:44.480
And for other eastern and northern parts,
dry and mostly sunny weather expected

00:02:44.480 --> 00:02:47.880
from Maria Island up through Swansea
and St Helens and then around

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:52.080
the north coast through Launceston, Devonport,
Burnie and Wynyard.

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:53.160
There will be a general

00:02:53.160 --> 00:02:56.920
air of cloudiness across the southern part
of South Australia on Thursday.

00:02:56.920 --> 00:03:00.120
That's the case across the south-east,
through the peninsulas, the islands,

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:03.720
the southern ranges, really
all of those southern growing regions.

00:03:03.720 --> 00:03:07.480
Fairly cloudy,
maybe a spot of light drizzle as well,

00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:11.280
but certainly nothing significant
accumulating in your rain gauge.

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:14.560
Further north, bright sunny skies,
with temperatures a little cooler

00:03:14.560 --> 00:03:17.880
than they've been over recent days
across the pastoral districts,

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:21.720
through parts of the Flinders, the,
the Riverland and the Murraylands.

00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:26.960
A dry, bright, mostly sunny day expected
in Perth with a high of 29°C

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:29.800
and it's a similar story
right along the west coast.

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:33.280
Showers down in the south, with the
possibility of some rain and thunderstorms

00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:38.120
to areas east of Kalgoorlie-Boulder, out
towards the Eucla and southern interior.

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:41.000
Further north,
sunny skies expected across the Pilbara

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:43.800
with a low risk of an afternoon
shower or thunderstorm.

00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:47.320
The risk is much higher through these parts

00:03:47.320 --> 00:03:50.400
for some rainfall on Thursday,
particularly between Darwin

00:03:50.400 --> 00:03:54.040
and Tennant Creek, where we could see
some widespread storm activity building,

00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:57.600
through the course of the day.
That could bring some heavy falls,

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:02.280
and that may lead to renewed rises along
our flooded rivers across the Top End.

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:07.040
So, perhaps some of those rivers
will take a few extra days to subside.

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:09.960
Some wet conditions are also expected
around the northern Kimberley,

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:12.760
but from Broome southwards
it should be a bright, clear day

00:04:12.760 --> 00:04:16.000
as it will be around
central parts of the country.

00:04:16.440 --> 00:04:18.240
And that's the wrap for now.

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:21.840
You can always get more weather info
on the BOM website or the BOM weather app

00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:25.160
or you can check in with us again
for tomorrow's National Weather Forecast.

